Operational Snapshot

The Right Companies, LLC focuses on evidence-driven investigations and practical security advisory work. Engagements are scoped tightly, executed quietly, and documented clearly.

About The Right Companies

A focused, standards-driven firm providing discreet investigative and security support throughout Florida.

The Right Companies, LLC is a Florida-based firm specializing in private investigations, security consulting, and risk management services. Founded and led by Richard S. Santini Lopez, the company supports private clients, corporations, and public-sector partners with disciplined, lawful, and confidential work. Each engagement is scoped clearly, executed to standard, and reported in a format that decision-makers and legal teams can actually use.

Services

Focused on what can be executed precisely, lawfully, and with a clear output.

Service Area 01
Private Investigations
Discreet, fact-driven support aligned with Florida law and client objectives.
  • Surveillance & activity checks
  • Background & due diligence investigations
  • Witness, claimant, and subject inquiries
  • OSINT and digital footprint analysis
Service Area 02
Security Consulting
Practical security guidance that reduces exposure instead of generating noise.
  • Facility and site vulnerability reviews
  • Policy and procedure assessments
  • Threat and risk evaluations
  • Executive and travel security planning
Service Area 03
Risk & Training Support
Support for organizations that need structure, documentation, and follow-through.
  • Risk mitigation and contingency planning
  • Internal incident and trend analysis
  • Risk and awareness training support
  • Coordination with legal and leadership teams

How Engagements Work

A simple, disciplined process that keeps expectations clear and work product clean.

Step 01
Initial Consultation
Clarify the problem, legal constraints, and objectives. Straight assessment of whether the case is a fit.
Step 02
Scope & Agreement
Define the scope, fees, and expected outputs in writing. Work does not begin without a clear, signed agreement.
Step 03
Execution
Conduct investigative or consulting work discreetly, document thoroughly, and stay aligned with Florida and U.S. law.
Step 04
Reporting & Follow-On
Deliver a clear report. Where relevant, outline follow-on options and risk considerations in plain language.
